<br>
There's a thread for lvls 29-33 with a great spot for mages to solo at those lvls:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2933.showMessage?topicID=71.topic">pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagi...D=71.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
And so did I.<br>
<br>
But the last 2 days I played again with my alt (lvl 21 Druid at the start) and was grouped with a Rogue (21 at start) and a warrior (22 at start).<br>
we wanted to move from Odus to LOIO so we came across Luclin. I then remembered echo caverns and told them about it. They were somewhat scared when I told them the MOBs would be lvl 23-25, but I could convince them to give it a try (basically I promised to stand there and die while they could run if something goes wrong ;-) )<br>
<br>
To say the result first: it was AWESOME. <br>
Every lvl was a breeze. Just imagine you kill yellow and red (most of them at 21/22 are red) MOBs in less than 2 minutes per MOB (including downtime; we killed the 7-8 Needlites (yellow/red) and 4 Boglings which are blue-yellow every 18 minutes (spawn time in there) )<br>
<br>
Yesterday I started out at lvl 22 (one blue into it) and 5 hours later I was lvl 23+3 yellows. I think that exp can only be toppped if somebody powerlevels you ;-)<br>
<br>
Now, we as a mage aren't the perfect choice for a group there...but if YOU have the idea and get others to there...they have to follow you ;-)<br>
Your main role would be of course to cast DS. The MObs simply and quickly kill themselves. You could also offer some added safety with your Pet, but still...A druid+Tank is much more perfect (I said we were there with a Rogue, but that wasn't really necessary) because Druid can DS, heal and snare (very, very nice!) and the Tank never was in danger of dying.<br>
<br>
So, get a good tank. (preferably Warrior in here, but everybody with a lot HPs and decent AC will do ;-) ).<br>
Get a healer (preferably no druid, except you are good friend with him, because with a druid you would soon feel that you aren't needed at all, they could do everything as well without you). so Tank+Mage+Cleric would be great in there and you will probably get the bext xp you can get at those lvls.<br>
<br>
Anyway...don't be scraed of the red MOBs with a good small group there...and get to lvl 24 in no time ;-) <p><img SRC="http://www.euphorion.org/sig/euph_zdd2.jpg"> </p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm42.showPrevMessage?topicID=16.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm42.showNextMessage?topicID=16.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm42.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm42.threadControl?topicID=16.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm42.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=16.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm42.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=16.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="themagicianstowerfrm45">User Interface<option value="themagicianstowerspells">Spells<option value="themagicianstowerequipmentandquests">Quests<option value="the